Int32Collection Class

Definition

Represents a collection of Int32 values.

In this Article

Remarks

Members of this class behave exactly as described by the IList<T>, ICollection<T>, and IEnumerable<T> documentation, except that this implementation throws an ArgumentException if you attempt to insert null into the collection.

Freezable Features: Because it inherits from the Freezable class, the Int32Collection class provides several special features: Int32Collection objects can be declared as , shared among multiple objects, made read-only to improve performance, cloned, and made thread-safe. For more information about the different features provided by Freezable objects, see the Freezable Objects Overview.

XAML Attribute Usage

0

XAML Values

oneOrMoreKInt32Values
One or more Int32 values, with each pair delimited by a single comma and/or one or more spaces:

Int32 [delimeter Int32 ]\*

For example, "5 10 43" and "5,10,43" are both valid.
